There is no lack of big words in the letter from the WestLB board to the employees of the company.
By merging units of the Dusseldorf financial institution with the Frankfurt Deka-Bank, "the central capital market house of the Savings Banks Finance Group" could be created, according to the letter that became known on Monday.
WestLB would bring a "competence block" with sustainable profitability to such a business.
And in general, such a connection could be the decisive impetus for further bundling in the Landesbank sector.
This is how it reads when a board wants to demonstrate its ability to act in difficult times.
Because the ailing WestLB is still under enormous pressure.
Not only on the part of the EU Commission, but also on the part of the Federal Financial Supervisory Authority, which recently made it clear to the North Rhine-Westphalian state government that time is pressing to find a solution for the future.
