This could involve the capital market business or parts of it.
Of course, according to the financial centre, the talks have only just begun.
This is not the first time that Deka-Bank, which with its 3,000 employees is one of the more important employers in the Financial Centre Frankfurt, has been mentioned when it comes to consolidation in the savings bank sector.
For a moment in 2003, it looked as if Deka-Bank could merge with Landesbank Rheinland-Pfalz and Helaba.
However, nothing came of this three-man alliance.
As soon as the plans became public, the Hessian state government spoke out against Helaba's participation in them.
The other two houses did not find each other either.
Landesbank Rheinland-Pfalz went instead to Landesbank Baden-Württemberg in Stuttgart.
But there have always been thought games about a connection of the Deka-Bank with Landesbanken.
Recently, however, Günther Merl, CEO of Helaba, had spoken out against simulation games about a merger with his company.
