Former Prime Minister of Bangladesh denied bail
A court in Bangladesh has rejected a bail request from former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, meaning she could be arrested if she returns to the country.
Her defence lawyers said the court refused bail on charges of extorting 50 million taka ($729,700) from a businessman while she was prime minister.
