BSKYB loses lawsuit in ITV case
BSkyB has lost its appeal against the Competition Commission's decision to reduce its stake in rival broadcaster ITV.
The Competition Court has ordered BSkyB to reduce its stake in ITV from 17.9% to below 7.5%.
Previously, the Commission had claimed that BskyB's share distorted competition and allowed it to exert an unfair influence on ITV.
