This news was overshadowed by new concerns that the financial crisis was far from over.
In the last chapter of the growing crisis, Citigroup is to buy the banking business of Wachovia Corporation, according to a government announcement on Monday.
In the meantime, the Belgian, Dutch and Luxembourg governments have partially nationalised the European financial group Fortis.
According to analysts at Barclays Capital, despite the tense negotiations that took place over the weekend and led to a bailout plan, it seems that it has not been possible to revive the mood in the markets.
As the economic situation continues to deteriorate, demand for goods, including oil, is expected to fall further.
Analysts at Deutsche Bank have written in a note to investors that forecasts for global capital markets, interest rates and exchange rates have become extremely uncertain.
We believe, they write, that the goods markets will also be affected.
"From a goods market perspective, what we're most concerned about is whether the U.S. virus is spreading globally, particularly to China."
